Lionel Messi Scores Record 50th Goal for Barcelona; AC Milan Extends Lead

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-04-23T20:14:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-23/lionel-messi-scores-record-50th-goal-for-barcelona-ac-milan-extends-lead.html
Lionel Messi  scored his 50th goal
of the season as Barcelona beat Osasuna 2-0 to continue its run
to the championship in Spain’s Primera Liga.  Messi became the first player to total 50 goals in Spain
when he scored in the 87th minute.  David Villa  had the other
goal as Barcelona stayed eight points ahead of Real Madrid with
five matches left. Real defeated Valencia 6-3 behind Gonzalo
Higuain’s hat trick.  AC Milan beat Brescia 1-0 to extend its lead to eight
points in Italy’s Serie A. Robinho scored for Milan, which needs
just four points from its final four matches to capture its 18th
league title. Inter Milan beat Lazio 2-1 to jump into second
place over Lazio, which lost 2-1 at Palermo.  Bayer Leverkusen  kept its title hopes alive in the German
Bundisliga with a 2-1 win over Hoffenheim. Leverkusen pulls to
within five points of leader Dortmund, which lost 1-0 at
Monchengladbach, with three games left.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  